= Notes
From the "Predicting Visual Fixations" paper: their paper simplifies the problem into 2D "video space", but we need to extend that back out to 3D space by casting rays and defining collision functions.

BIGGER PROBLEM: We need to adjust our probability function to account for fixed time sampling, rather than saccadic sampling. Would be a lot easier if we had an eye tracking solution, but that imposes hardware limitations. Most simple solution would be to integrate over all likely gaze positions.

